messages.message: Heyt @Paul H I'm getting typescript errors locally due to `websocketConfig` not being defined. It seems to stem from your PR here (https://github.com/instabase/instabase/pull/67359) where you change the `utils.js` file in `webpack`. You reference `websocketConfig` before its defined it seems.
I think you just meant to use the `hotreloadConfig` var defined above instead
I have a fix in my PR here, but if you want to make a tiny fix PR instead then that is fine too: https://github.com/instabase/instabase/pull/67456

Thanks for finding this, I created a small PR just to unblock master:
https://github.com/instabase/instabase/pull/67477
Thanks this may also be messing up crafting right now

But I’ll take a deeper dive into that box.
